<br>
When I ran out of power and got bored of just resing I saw a yellow elf off to the side of their lines a bit. I knew it was a trap but I decided to teach the elf a lesson so I went to the end of our line and ran at him from the side. I started getting pelted with weak arrows about ½ way there and got next to the guy and wacked him for about ½ of his HP in one shot. He started running and the arrows we’re hitting for over 100 HP now so I ran back towards my line. I made it most of the way back and was in res range so my cleric friend resed me.<br>
<br>
I sat down and recovered from this and then go back up and started resing people again. I would inch out and try to get people who died on their side of the battle. Some little orange Lukrien archer decided I was doing something wrong so started following me and pelting me with arrows every time I tried to res from to far out. Well, I was trying to res a guy and the battle shifted and left this little archer all alone. I rushed across the line, took a good shot on the way, but got there and whacked her for about 1/3 of her HP in one shot. She realized she was alone and started to run. I was then being pelted with arrows again so I ran back and made it a bit further across the field before I ate some more dirt.<br>
<br>
I recovered from that res and the battle turned in our favor. We broke their lines and it was general melee. I rushed in and found a half dead orange Firbog that had a round wood shield and proceeded to make him all dead. I guess he was confused. I ran up and he turned to fight. I smacked him and he just stood there then ran after my second hit. I guess I don’t look like a fighter that can take ½ his HP in 3 hits.<br>
